</Header><BillAmendment><Body>
<P1 id="NC2"><Pnumber>NC2</Pnumber><P1para><Text><?start-line?>To move the following Clause:—</Text>

</P1para><BlockAmendment Format="None" context="clause"><Text><?start-line?>‘Suppliers are not allowed to refer cases to the Adjudicator and cannot have cases <?new-line?>referred on their behalf if their turnover exceeds £1bn per annum.’.</Text>
</BlockAmendment></P1>
<?new-line?><P1 id="NC3"><Pnumber>NC3</Pnumber><P1para><Text><?start-line?>To move the following Clause:—</Text>

</P1para><BlockAmendment Format="None" context="clause"><Text><?start-line?>‘This Bill will expire in seven years from the date it receives Royal Assent.’.</Text>
</BlockAmendment></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00024"><Pnumber>24</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end add—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end add]?><?new-page?><P2>
<Pnumber>4</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The large retailer may appeal against the requirement to publish information—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>to the High Court, in England and Wales or Northern Ireland; or</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>to the Court of Session, in Scotland.’.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00025"><Pnumber>25</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end add—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end add]?><?new-page?><P3>
<Pnumber>d</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>all costs incurred by the Adjudicator.’.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00026"><Pnumber>26</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end add—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end add]?><?new-page?><P2>
<Pnumber>3A</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>For the purpose of the first levy and any subsequent annual increase in the levy <?new-line?>of greater then 10 per cent on the previous year, the Adjudicator must undertake <?new-line?>a consultation process with the large retailers and consider any submissions <?new-line?>received as the Adjudicator considers appropriate.’.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-line?><P1 id="NC4"><Pnumber>NC4</Pnumber><P1para><Text><?start-line?>To move the following Clause:—</Text>

</P1para><BlockAmendment Format="None" context="clause"><Text><?start-line?>‘Suppliers are not allowed to refer cases to the Adjudicator and cannot have cases <?new-line?>referred on their behalf if they have their principal headquarters outside the <?new-line?>European Union.’.</Text>
</BlockAmendment></P1>
<?new-line?><P1 id="NC5"><Pnumber>NC5</Pnumber><P1para><Text><?start-line?>To move the following Clause:—</Text>

</P1para><BlockAmendment Format="None" context="clause"><Text><?start-line?>‘The provisions of this Act shall not apply to any supplies which are produced, <?new-line?>manufactured or processed, in whole or in part, outside the European Union.’.</Text>
</BlockAmendment></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00027"><Pnumber>27</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>leave out lines 35 to 40 and insert ‘This Act shall come into force <?new-line?>two months after Royal Assent.’.</Text>

<?new-line?>
</P1para></P1>
<?new-line?><P1 id="p00008"><Pnumber>8</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>leave out lines 34 to 36 and insert—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [leave out lines 34 to 36 and insert]?><?new-page?><P2>
<Pnumber>10A</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The Secretary of State may by order provide that this Act has effect as if the <?new-line?>section set out in subsection (11) below were inserted after section 4.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>10B</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>An order under subsection (10A)—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>may be made only if, as a result of the findings of a review, the Secretary <?new-line?>of State thinks that making the order would enable the Adjudicator to be <?new-line?>more effective;</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>may be revoked only if, as a result of the findings of a review, the <?new-line?>Secretary of State thinks that revoking the order would not impair the <?new-line?>Adjudicator’s effectiveness.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2>
<Pnumber>11</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>This is the section referred to in subsection (10A)—’.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1><A2A id="a0000a" amendmentId="p00008"><PNumber>(a)</PNumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>after ‘more’, insert ‘efficient and’.</Text>
</P1para></A2A><A2A id="a0000b" amendmentId="p00008"><PNumber>(b)</PNumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>after ‘Adjudicator’s’, insert ‘efficiency and’.</Text>
</P1para></A2A>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00028"><Pnumber>28</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end insert—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end insert]?><?new-page?><P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>the nature and type of arbitrations to be conducted under section 3 <?new-line?>including:</Text>
<P4>
<Pnumber>i</Pnumber>
<P4para>
<Text><?start-line?>the law applicable to an arbirtration; and</Text>
</P4para>
</P4>
<P4>
<Pnumber>ii</Pnumber>
<P4para>
<Text><?start-line?>where the arbitration should be conducted.’.</Text>
</P4para>
</P4>
</P3para>
</P3>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00029"><Pnumber>29</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end add—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end add]?><?new-page?><P2>
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>The Office of Fair Trading shall be required to publish a response to the <?new-line?>Adjudicator on the recommendations set out in subsection (1) explaining whether <?new-line?>they will be acted upon or not.’.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00030"><Pnumber>30</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>at end add—</Text>
<BlockAmendment Format="single" Context="clause" TargetClass="unknown" TargetSubClass="unknown"><?Text [at end add]?><?new-page?><P2>
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text><?start-line?>In assessing changes that could be made to the Code, the Adjudicator shall give <?new-line?>due consideration to—</Text>
<P3>
<Pnumber>a</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>the territorial extent of the Code, especially in relation to activities of <?new-line?>large retailers outwith the UK, including work done by subsidiaries of <?new-line?>large retailers;</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>b</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>whether intermediaries in the supply chain should be covered; and</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
<P3>
<Pnumber>c</Pnumber>
<P3para>
<Text><?start-line?>whether commercial pressures or criminal activity pose risks to <?new-line?>consumer interests by potentially compromising standards of food safety, <?new-line?>hygiene and food authenticity.’.</Text>
</P3para>
</P3>
</P2para>
</P2>
</BlockAmendment></P1para></P1>
<?new-page?><P1 id="p00031"><Pnumber>31</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>after ‘followed’, insert ‘and whether any further <?new-line?>enforcement measures are to be taken in order to secure compliance with the Groceries <?new-line?>Code.’.</Text>

<?new-line?>

<?new-line?>
</P1para></P1>
<?new-line?><P1 id="p00032"><Pnumber>32</Pnumber><?quote []?><P1para><Text><?start-line?>leave out subsection (11).</Text>
</P1para></P1>

</Body></BillAmendment>
